<p>I find myself doing this often:</p>  <ul> <li><p>launch emacs</p></li> <li><p>shh into a server by <code>C-x C-f [RET] /ssh:me@aserver.com:filetoedit.py [RET]</code></p></li> <li><p><code>C-x 2</code> to split windows</p></li> <li><p><code>C-x o</code> to switch to top window</p></li> <li><p><code>M-x shell</code> to start a shell on my ssh connection</p></li> </ul>  <p>I there a way to automatically replicate this process on startup? <code>M-x desktop-save</code> doesn't seem to be doing this for me.</p>